      • join

        public History join(@NonNull
           Processor creator,
           @NonNull
           Set<History> toJoin)
        Description copied from class: History
        Create a History object after this one, which has been branched off and processed concurrently and now needs to be joined together.

        The supplied set of History objects were produced by the final Processors in the branches, and if those same History objects appear another call to this.join(..), the same History object is returned.

        Specified by:
        join in class History
        Returns:

      • isJoinPoint

        public boolean isJoinPoint()
        Description copied from class: History
        If this object was created by history.join(..) then it is a join point, and the History objects that were joined are accessible with history.getJoined().

        Calling getPrevious() on the returned History object yields this object. The branched/joined History objects are only accessible through the returned object.

        Specified by:
        isJoinPoint in class History
        Returns:
        true iff this is a join point of other histories.
